strings.Value: "Now I am the lawful ruler of these lands."
"What will you do now?"
"I hope you haven't been attacking the neighboring villages and settlements..."
"I met some other kobolds nearby."
"Tartuk has appeared in my lands again. Has he come to you?"
[Attack] "Our alliance seems to have been a mistake. I have no wish to see kobolds in my lands!"
[Leave] "Farewell, Chief!"
"You once asked me to deal with Queen Bdaah. I have defeated her."
"Greetingsss, friend! Your visssit joy!"
"Your! Sit! Oy!"
"You become Chief? Good!"
"Come! Chief! Oood!"
"We take mite dungeon. Much ssspace, many kobold. Niccce! Kobold power grow."
"Mite invite us feassst. Gave raw sssquirrel with hide. Mite ssstupid. If we war, kobold winsss!"
"We honor new sssacred thhhing! It bring luck! Kobold ssstrong, catch many fisssh, ssscare human, take loot!"
{n}The Chief seems absorbed in thought.{/n} "We attack one human bandit. Doesssn't count."
"Not our tribe. We throw weaklingsss out!"
"Throw! Out!" {n}The crier seems particularly excited, and repeats the two words flawlessly.{/n}
"Hideousss liar! Sssend messsenger. Say — he king. I sssay I ssskin Tartuk!" {n}The Chief shakes his weapon angrily.{/n} "Never let him here. No ssstrange kobold!"
"Let! Kobold! Trange!"
{n}The Chief scratches the back of his head with his claw.{/n} "You don't wishhh peaccce with mite? Good. I promissse honorsss for victory over Queen — I keep promissse!"
"Honorsss for victory!"
